{"key":"processedPost-8619129","value":{"id":8619129,"first":8609313,"last":8623189,"when":1215741286,"utime":"07/11/08 04:54 AM","cleanedPost":"I think what prisoner was referring to was letting it fruit right from the pvc log.&nbsp; I've done those with 3/8\" holes drilled four inches apart down the length of the pipe.&nbsp; Tape over the holes with micropore tape during colonization, and then remove the tape for fruiting.&nbsp; If you use that method, alternate spawn and straw while packing, and pack it with most of your weight.<br />Straw has to be cut into 1\" to 4\" pieces to make it easier for the mycelium to penetrate into the center.&nbsp; We can pack it tight because there's so much air in straw, as you can see from the microscope picture below of a cross section of a piece of wheat straw.<br />RR<br /><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-006/108452877-SEM_of_Straw.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/07-006/108452877-thumb_SEM_of_Straw.jpg\"></a>"}}